bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Organized athletics have been a part of The George Washington University since the late nineteenth century. The Department of Athletics and Recreation is headed by a Director of Athletics, who oversees the following units: Administration, Academic Support, Recreational Sports, Athletics Communications (sports information and community outreach), Sports Medicine, Baseball, Basketball (men's and women's), Rowing (crew), Cross Country, Golf, Gymnastics, Lacrosse (women's), Soccer (men's and women's), Softball (women's), Squash (men's and women's), Swimming & Diving, Tennis (men's and women's), Volleyball, Water Polo (men's and women's). Before 1988 their were separate Departments for men and women's athletics. The Director of Athletics reports to the Vice President for Student and Academic Support Services. The Department publishes annual media guides for varsity sports.
N.B. This history note was written in 2005

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection include media guides, films, brochures, videotapes, uniforms, artifacts, football programs, statistics, magazines, photographs, trophies, newsletters, and news releases. They range in date from 1907-2011, and were transferred to the University Archives by the Director of the Department of Athletics.
Formerly RG 6.4.2; there is no series 15.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into forty-three series: George Washington sports information collection; Basketball films; Guides, programs, notebooks, and Hatchets; Newspaper clippings; Videotapes; Uniforms; Certificate and photograph; Newspaper clippings; Programs, guides, posters, profiles, and shirt; Football team photographs; Women's rifle club collection; Trophies; Program and ticket; Jump rope; William Reinhart, papers; Banners; Cheerleader uniforms; Bill Ryan football memorabilia; Letterman's sweaters; Basketball ephemera; Football ponchos; Colonials Sports News; Intramural sports handbooks; Colonial Cager newspaper; Athletic uniforms and George mascot costume; George mascot heads and costumes; Athletic uniforms and artifacts; Blanket, sweater, and jersey; Sports media guides; Football programs; Basketball memorabilia; Shirts; Basketball memorabilia; Women's volleyball videotapes; Basketball memorabilia; Jerseys, programs, letter, and magazine; Departmental files; videotapes; athletic uniforms and memorabilia; basketball game programs and media guides; sports media guides, posters, basketball programs and jerseys.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists football media guides and game statistics, brochures, meeting minutes, news letters, magazines, scrapbooks, film, videotape, memorabilia, and news clippings. Subjects include: football, wrestling, rifle, sports clubs, Colonials, Inc. (a booster club), and women's athletics.
They range in date from 1930-93, and were transferred to the University Archives by the Director of the Department of Athletics in 1996.
Formerly ACC#552, formerly RG6.4

odd.head: General note
odd.p: GW football jersey , number 20, ca. 1933. This textile has blue sleeves with red and cream stripes (refered to as "hard jersey" style in the football programs). This applique style jersey consists of a number 20 sown onto a cream colored background and red stripes along the bottom portion. Also attached to the bottom edge of this jersey, are buttons which would enclose the front and back of the uniform. This jersey is believed to have belonged to football player Benedict Plotnicki (#20 in 1933). By 1935 this style jersey was retired. Originally on exhibit in the David S. Brown Memorabilia Room.
